Package: OncoImplexus
Type: Package
Title: Integrated Detection of Complex Chromosomal Rearrangements in Cancer
Version: 1.3.0
Date: 2025-01-18
Author: Chia-Chun Chiu, Wei-Sheng Wu, Chien-Feng Li
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chia-Chun", "Chiu", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "n28111021@gs.ncku.edu.tw", comment = "Package maintainer, Chromoplexy/Chromoanasynthesis algorithms"),
    person("Wei-Sheng", "Wu", role = "aut", comment = "Author"),
    person("Chien-Feng", "Li", role = "aut", comment = "Author"))
Maintainer: Chia-Chun Chiu <n28111021@gs.ncku.edu.tw>
Description: OncoImplexus is a comprehensive framework for detecting and classifying
    complex chromosomal rearrangements (chromoanagenesis) in cancer genomes.
    It integrates detection modules for Chromothripsis (adapted from ShatterSeek),
    Chromoplexy (novel graph-based chaining algorithm), and Chromoanasynthesis
    (topology-based replication analysis). Features include direct VCF support,
    advanced visualization (genome dashboards, circos plots), and mechanistic
    classification of mixed events.
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0), methods, BiocGenerics, foreach, graph, S4Vectors
